Ryan,
we are all kindred spirits on the Read Alphabet group on Yahoo. As such, 
I&#39;m curious to know the answer to the following question from you and 
anyone on the group.

In the Read Alphabet, how do you, personally, write the second syllable 
of the word February? Do you use letters 2-25-40, or 2-17-40? I 
pronounce it the way it is spelled. This makes me a little peculiar, 
since most people say what they hear other people say without regard to 
the spelling.
Vin
